.SH "NAME"
gitcommitizen \- configuration file for conventional commit linting
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fB.gitcommitizen\fP file defines commit message types, scopes, and validation
settings for conventional commits. It uses INI\-style configuration with three
sections: settings, scopes, and types.
.SH "FILE FORMAT"
.sp
INI\-style configuration with three sections:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[settings]
require\-scope = false
defined\-scope = false
enforce\-patterns = false
multi\-scope = false

[scopes]
name = glob\-pattern[, glob\-pattern]...

[types]
name = description
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Settings"
.sp
\fBrequire\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Require a scope to be present (default: false). When enabled:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBcreate\fP: Removes the "(none)" option; scope is mandatory.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBlint\fP: Fails if commit has no scope.
Can be overridden by \f(CR\-r\fP or \f(CR\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP flags.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBdefined\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Require scope to be defined in configuration (default: false). When enabled:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBcreate\fP: Removes the "(custom)" option; only configured scopes allowed.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBlint\fP: Fails if scope is not in \f(CR[scopes]\fP.
Can be overridden by \f(CR\-d\fP or \f(CR\-\-no\-defined\-scope\fP flags.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBenforce\-patterns\fP
.RS 4
Enforce scope\-file pattern matching (default: false). When enabled:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Requires scope to match file patterns from \f(CR[scopes]\fP when \f(CR\-\-paths\fP is provided.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Implies \f(CRdefined\-scope = true\fP (scope must exist in config).
Can be overridden by \f(CR\-e\fP or \f(CR\-\-no\-enforce\-patterns\fP flags.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBmulti\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Allow multiple scopes like \f(CRfeat(api,db):\fP (default: false).
Can be overridden by \f(CR\-m\fP or \f(CR\-\-no\-multi\-scope\fP flags.
.RE
.SS "Scopes"
.sp
Maps scope names to glob patterns. Multiple patterns are separated by commas.
When validating with \f(CR\-\-files\fP, the scope is checked against these patterns
to ensure commits use appropriate scopes for the files being changed.
.sp
Special scope \f(CR*\fP matches any files (wildcard). This allows any scope to be used
regardless of which files are staged.
.SS "Types"
.sp
Maps type names to their descriptions. These are shown during interactive commit
creation and used for validation.
.SH "SYNTAX"
.sp
Lines starting with \f(CR#\fP or \f(CR;\fP are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
Whitespace around \f(CR=\fP is optional.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[settings]
require\-scope = true
defined\-scope = true
enforce\-patterns = true
multi\-scope = true

[scopes]
# API and database scopes
api = src/api/**, tests/api/**
db = src/db/**, migrations/**
ui = src/components/**, src/pages/**
docs = docs/**, *.md
* = .github/**, scripts/**

[types]
feat = A new feature
fix = A bug fix
docs = Documentation only changes
style = Code style changes (formatting, semicolons)
refactor = Code refactoring without behavior change
perf = Performance improvements
test = Adding or updating tests
build = Build system or dependencies
ci = CI/CD configuration changes
chore = Maintenance tasks
revert = Revert a previous commit
.fam
.fi
